What each change does
internal/analyticsapi/domain/narrative.go
adds the NarrativeStore interface
adds the shared ErrNarrativeNotFound
adds the helper that builds the object-store key: summary/cids/{cid}.md

internal/analyticsapi/gateways/repos/narrative_store.go
adds the real minio-backed summary reader
this is where the analytics API reads the markdown summary from object storage

internal/analyticsapi/usecase/narrative/narrative.go
stopped returning Hello World
now asks the store for the summary by CID

internal/analyticsapi/gateways/api/api.go
now returns 404 when a summary does not exist
keeps 500 for real server/storage failures

cmd/analyticsapi/main.go
wires the real narrative store into the service

internal/analyticsapi/domain/config.go
adds S3_ACCESS_KEY and S3_SECRET_KEY

deploy/analyticsapi.yaml
passes minio credentials into the local analytics API deployment

go.mod and go.sum
add the minio client dependency needed for object-store access

Why this structure
I kept the design layered:
domain/ = shared contract and key-building rule
usecase/narrative/ = “get summary for CID”
gateways/repos/ = actual minio object-store reading
cmd/analyticsapi/ = dependency wiring only
That keeps the API route thin and avoids putting storage logic directly in the handler.
